		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />He shiru, how do you handle such thing with 16 color mode, i'm curious. You write to tile adress and map the tiles to vram ? <br />I think we can reduce time if we use mode 7 with low resolution (for example 128x64 only and zoom it). Will be nice to know how to do that to have a &quot;spout&quot; game for example <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /><br /><br />Regarding source code, last version is here : <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://code.google.com/p/pvsneslib/source/browse/#svn%2Ftrunk%2Fpvsneslib%2Fsource">https://code.google.com/p/pvsneslib/sou ... b%2Fsource</a><!-- m --><br /><br />To transfert a complete image, just take a look at Background/Mode3 example, you've got everything to do that. You only need to have your picture with correct format.

		

